his object represents.\n37:             type: string\n38:           metadata:\n39:             type: object\n40:           spec:\n41:             description: CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of a CodeInterpreter.\n42:             type: object\n43:             properties:\n44:               enabledPackages:\n45:                 description: EnabledPackages specifies allowed packages for the interpreter.\n46:                 type: array\n47:                 items:\n48:                   type: string\n49:               env:\n50:                 description: Env defines environment variables to inject into the interpreter container.\n51:                 type: array\n52:                 items:\n53:                   type: object\n54:                   properties:\n55:                     name:\n56:                       type: string\n57:                     value:\n58:                       type: string\n59:               image:\n60:                 description: Image is the container image for the interpreter.\n61:                 type: string\n62:               resources:\n63:                 description: Resources defines compute resource requirements for the interpreter container.\n64:                 type: object\n65:                 properties:\n66:                   limits:\n67:                     type: object\n68:                   requests:\n69:                     type: object\n70:               runtime:\n71:                 default: python\n72:                 description: Runtime specifies the execution environment type.\n73:                 enum:\n74:                 - python\n75:                 - javascript\n76:                 - typescript\n77:                 - go\n78:                 type: string\n79:               timeout:\n80:                 default: 5m\n81:                 description: Timeout defines the maximum execution time for code snippets.\n82:                 type: string\n83:             required:\n84:             - image\n85:           status:\n86:             description: CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of a CodeInterpreter.\n87:             type: object\n88:             properties:\n89:               conditions:\n90:                 description: Conditions represent the latest available observations of a CodeInterpreter's current state.\n91:                 type: array\n92:                 items:\n93:                   type: object\n94:                   properties:\n95:                     lastTransitionTime:\n96:                       format: date-time\n97:                       type: string\n98:                     message:\n99:                       type: string\n100:                     reason:\n101:                       type: string\n102:                     status:\n103:                       type: string\n104:                     type:\n105:                       type: string\n106:                     observedGeneration:\n107:                       format: int64\n108:                       type: integer\n109:               observedGeneration:\n110:                 format: int64\n111:                 type: integer\n112:               ready:\n113:                 description: Ready indicates whether the interpreter is ready to execute code.\n114:                 type: boolean\n115:     subresources:\n116:       status: {}\n117:     additionalPrinterColumns:\n118:     - name: Ready\n119:       type: boolean\n120:       jsonPath: .status.ready\n121:     - name: Runtime\n122:       type: string\n123:       jsonPath: .spec.runtime\n124:     - name: Age\n125:       type: date\n126:       jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n127: {{- end }}\n\n(End of file - total 127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\napiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\nkind: CustomResourceDefinition\nmetadata:\n  name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n  annotations:\n    helm.sh/hook: crd-install\n    helm.sh/hook-weight: \"-5\"