{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899878907,"sessionID":"ses_28420c30cffepE7vemUlRXG8Kj","part":{"id":"prt_d7be1a594001RfjMkIpnKrFMuu","messageID":"msg_d7be01abf001kAcyFEvYmROBdm","sessionID":"ses_28420c30cffepE7vemUlRXG8Kj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-15f7550e4090438cadf84c889f0e1091","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Design: AR-043 — AgentCube Architecture Design and API Documentation\n\n## Overview\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native AI agent runtime platform that provides tools for building, deploying, and managing AI agent workloads. The platform consists of a Python SDK, CLI tools, and Kubernetes custom resources that together enable a complete agent development lifecycle.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Developer Layer                              │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n│  │   Python SDK │  │   CLI Tools  │  │  kubectl plg │              │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      AgentCube Platform                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                    Control Plane                              │  │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │  │\n│  │  │ Workload Mgr │  │ Controller   │  │ CRD Manager  │      │  │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                    Data Plane                                 │  │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │  │\n│  │  │    Router    │  │    Picod     │  │ Session Store│      │  │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Kubernetes Cluster                              │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n│  │ AgentRuntime │  │CodeInterpreter│  │Agent Workload│              │\n│  │    CRDs      │  │    CRDs       │  │   Pods       │              │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n#### Python SDK Layer\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── __init__.py\n├── agent_runtime.py           # Agent runtime client\n├── code_interpreter.py        # Code interpreter client\n├── exceptions.py              # Exception hierarchy\n├── clients/\n│   ├── control_plane.py       # Control plane API client\n│   ├── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    # Agent runtime data plane client\n│   └── code_interpreter_data_plane.py # Code interpreter data plane client\n└── utils/\n    ├── http.py                # HTTP session management\n    ├── log.py                 # Logging utilities\n    └── utils.py               # Common utilities\n```\n\n#### CLI Layer\n\n```\ncmd/cli/agentcube/\n├── cli/\n│   └── main.py                # CLI entry point with Typer\n├── runtime/\n│   ├── pack_runtime.py        # Packaging logic\n│   ├── build_runtime.py       # Image building logic\n│   ├── publish_runtime.py     # Publishing logic\n│   ├── invoke_runtime.py      # Invocation logic\n│   └── status_runtime.py      # Status query logic\n├── providers/\n│   ├── base.py                # Base provider interface\n│   ├── k8s_provider.py        # Kubernetes provider\n│   └── agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCube provider\n├── services/\n│   ├── metadata_service.py    # Metadata management\n│   └── docker_service.py      # Docker operations\n└── models/\n    └── pack_models.py         # Data models\n```\n\n#### Platform Layer\n\n```\ncmd/agentcube/\n└── main.go                    # Controller manager entry point\n\npkg/\n├── controller/                # Kubernetes controllers\n├── router/                    # Request routing\n├── store/                     # Session storage\n└── picod/                     # Code execution\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Python SDK Data Structures\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    \"\"\"Client for Agent Runtime invocation.\"\"\"\n    \n    agent_name: str\n    namespace: str\n    router_url: str\n    session_id: str\n    timeout: int\n    connect_timeout: float\n    verbose: bool\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    \"\"\"Main client for Code Interpreter session management.\"\"\"\n    \n    name: str\n    namespace: str\n    ttl: int\n    workload_manager_url: str\n    router_url: str\n    auth_token: str\n    session_id: str\n    verbose: bool\n```\n\n#### AgentMetadata (Pydantic Model)\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Agent metadata model.\"\"\"\n    \n    agent_name: str\n    description: str | None\n    language: str = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: str\n    port: int = 8080\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"\n    region: str | None\n    version: str | None\n    image: dict[str, Any] | None\n    auth: dict[str, Any] | None\n    requirements_file: str | None = \"requirements.txt\"\n    registry_url: str | None\n    registry_username: str | None\n    registry_password: str | None\n    agent_endpoint: str | None\n    workload_manager_url: str | None\n    router_url: str | None\n    readiness_probe_path: str | None\n    readiness_probe_port: int | None\n    agent_id: str | None\n    session_id: str | None\n    k8s_deployment: dict[str, Any] | None\n```\n\n#### DeploymentResult\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass DeploymentResult:\n    \"\"\"Deployment result data class.\"\"\"\n    \n    status: ProviderStatus\n    agent_name: str\n    namespace: str\n    resource_url: str | None\n    metadata: dict[str, Any]\n    error: str | None\n```\n\n#### AgentStatus\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass AgentStatus:\n    \"\"\"Agent status data class.\"\"\"\n    \n    status: ProviderStatus\n    agent_name: str\n    namespace: str\n    replicas: int | None\n    ready_replicas: int | None\n    available_replicas: int | None\n    resource_type: str | None\n    metadata: dict[str, Any]\n    error: str | None\n```\n\n#### ProviderStatus\n\n```python\nclass ProviderStatus(str, Enum):\n    \"\"\"Provider status enumeration.\"\"\"\n    \n    PENDING = \"pending\"\n    DEPLOYING = \"deploying\"\n    RUNNING = \"running\"\n    FAILED = \"failed\"\n    NOT_FOUND = \"not_found\"\n    ERROR = \"error\"\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Custom Resources\n\n#### AgentRuntime CRD\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: example-agent\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  maxSessionDuration: 8h\n  podTemplate:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: example-agent\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: agent\n        image: example/agent:latest\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\nstatus:\n  conditions:\n  - type: Ready\n    status: \"True\"\n    lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n    reason: DeploymentReady\n    message: Deployment is ready\n  observedGeneration: 1\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter CRD\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: CodeInterpreter\nmetadata:\n  name: example-interpreter\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  image: python:3.10-slim\n  runtime: python\n  timeout: 5m\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: \"2\"\n      memory: \"2Gi\"\n    requests:\n      cpu: \"1\"\n      memory: \"1Gi\"\n  enabledPackages:\n  - numpy\n  - pandas\n  env:\n  - name: PYTHONPATH\n    value: /usr/local/lib/python3.10/site-packages\nstatus:\n  ready: true\n  conditions:\n  - type: Ready\n    status: \"True\"\n    lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  observedGeneration: 1\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Control Plane API\n\n#### Create Session\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /v1/code-interpreter`\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"ttl\": 3600,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"labels\": {\n      \"env\": \"dev\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"uuid-session-id\",\n  \"status\": \"created\"\n}\n```\n\n**Headers**:\n- `Authorization`: `Bearer <token>`\n\n#### Delete Session\n\n**Endpoint**: `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}`\n\n**Response**:\n- Status Code: `204 No Content`\n\n**Headers**:\n- `Authorization`: `Bearer <token>`\n\n### Data Plane API (Agent Runtime)\n\n#### Bootstrap Session\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agentName}/invocations/`\n\n**Response Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n\n**Response Body**: Empty\n\n#### Invoke Agent\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agentName}/invocations/`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n- `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Hello, agent!\",\n  \"context\": {\n    \"user\": \"test-user\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"response\": \"Hello! How can I help you today?\",\n  \"status\": \"success\"\n}\n```\n\n### Data Plane API (Code Interpreter)\n\n#### Execute Command\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/execute`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n- `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('Hello')\"],\n  \"timeout\": \"30s\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"stdout\": \"Hello\\n\",\n  \"stderr\": \"\",\n  \"exit_code\": 0\n}\n```\n\n#### Write File\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n- `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"/workspace/test.py\",\n  \"content\": \"base64-encoded-content\",\n  \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response**: Status `200 OK`\n\n#### List Files\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n\n**Query Parameters**:\n- `path`: Directory path (default: \".\")\n\n**Response Body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"test.py\",\n      \"path\": \"/workspace/test.py\",\n      \"size\": 1024,\n      \"mode\": \"0644\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"directories\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"data\",\n      \"path\": \"/workspace/data\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### Download File\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files/{path}`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n\n**Response**: File content (binary stream)\n\n#### Upload File\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files`\n\n**Request Headers**:\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n\n**Request Body**: `multipart/form-data`\n- `file`: File content\n- `path`: Target path\n- `mode`: File permissions (default: \"0644\")\n\n**Response**: Status `200 OK`\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\n# Base exception\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n# Command execution errors\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when command execution fails.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: str | None = None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\n# Session management errors\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n# Data plane operation errors\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n**Standard Error Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\",\n    \"message\": \"Session ID 'xxx' not found or expired\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"sessionId\": \"xxx\",\n      \"ttl\": 3600\n    }\n  },\n  \"requestId\": \"uuid-request-id\"\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP Status Codes\n\n| Status Code | Description | Usage |\n|-------------|-------------|-------|\n| 200 | OK | Successful operation |\n| 201 | Created | Resource created successfully |\n| 204 | No Content | Successful operation with no response body |\n| 400 | Bad Request | Invalid request parameters |\n| 401 | Unauthorized | Missing or invalid authentication |\n| 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n| 404 | Not Found | Resource not found |\n| 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n| 429 | Too Many Requests | Rate limit exceeded |\n| 500 | Internal Server Error | Server-side error |\n| 503 | Service Unavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n\n### Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session ID not found or expired |\n| `SESSION_ALREADY_EXISTS` | 409 | Session with same name already exists |\n| `INVALID_SESSION_ID` | 400 | Invalid session ID format |\n| `COMMAND_EXECUTION_FAILED` | 500 | Command execution failed |\n| `TIMEOUT_EXCEEDED` | 504 | Operation timed out |\n| `UNAUTHORIZED_ACCESS` | 403 | Insufficient permissions |\n| `INVALID_REQUEST_BODY` | 400 | Invalid request JSON |\n| `UNSUPPORTED_LANGUAGE` | 400 | Unsupported programming language |\n| `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Requested file not found |\n| `INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES` | 503 | Insufficient cluster resources |\n\n### Retry Strategy\n\n**Exponential Backoff**:\n- Initial delay: 1 second\n- Maximum delay: 30 seconds\n- Maximum attempts: 3\n- Backoff factor: 2.0\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.providers.retry import retry_on_exception\n\n@retry_on_exception(\n    max_attempts=3,\n    delay=2.0,\n    exceptions=(ApiException,)\n)\ndef _wait_for_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Wait for deployment to be ready with retry logic.\"\"\"\n    # Implementation\n    pass\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Testing\n\n#### Python SDK Tests\n\n**Test Structure**:\n```\nagentcube/tests/\n├── __init__.py\n├── test_agent_runtime.py\n├── test_code_interpreter.py\n├── test_clients/\n│   ├── test_control_plane.py\n│   ├── test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n│   └── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n└── fixtures/\n    ├── mock_responses.py\n    └── test_data.py\n```\n\n**Test Framework**: `pytest`\n\n**Key Test Areas**:\n1. Client initialization and configuration\n2. Session lifecycle management\n3. Command execution and error handling\n4. File operations (write, read, upload, download)\n5. HTTP request/response handling\n6. Timeout and retry logic\n\n**Example Test**:\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_response():\n    response = Mock()\n    response.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-session-id\"}\n    response.headers = {}\n    return response\n\ndef test_create_session(mock_response):\n    with patch('requests.Session.post', return_value=mock_response):\n        client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n            name=\"test-interpreter\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            router_url=\"http://test-router\"\n        )\n        assert client.session_id == \"test-session-id\"\n\ndef test_execute_command_error():\n    client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n        name=\"test-interpreter\",\n        namespace=\"default\",\n        router_url=\"http://test-router\",\n        session_id=\"test-session-id\"\n    )\n    \n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_response.json.return_value = {\n        \"stdout\": \"\",\n        \"stderr\": \"Command failed\",\n        \"exit_code\": 1\n    }\n    \n    with patch('requests.Session.post', return_value=mock_response):\n        with pytest.raises(CommandExecutionError) as exc_info:\n            client.execute_command(\"false\")\n        assert exc_info.value.exit_code == 1\n```\n\n#### CLI Tests\n\n**Test Structure**:\n```\ncmd/cli/agentcube/tests/\n├── __init__.py\n├── test_cli.py\n├── test_runtime/\n│   ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n│   ├── test_build_runtime.py\n│   ├── test_publish_runtime.py\n│   ├── test_invoke_runtime.py\n│   └── test_status_runtime.py\n├── test_providers/\n│   ├── test_base_provider.py\n│   ├── test_k8s_provider.py\n│   └── test_agentcube_provider.py\n└── test_services/\n    ├── test_metadata_service.py\n    └── test_docker_service.py\n```\n\n**Test Framework**: `pytest` with `typer.testing`\n\n**Key Test Areas**:\n1. CLI command parsing and validation\n2. Runtime execution flow\n3. Provider deployment and status\n4. Metadata management\n5. Docker operations (mocked)\n6. Error handling and user feedback\n\n**Example Test**:\n```python\nfrom typer.testing import CliRunner\nfrom agentcube.cli.main import app\n\nrunner = CliRunner()\n\ndef test_pack_command():\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\n        \"pack\",\n        \"--workspace\", \"tests/fixtures/sample-agent\",\n        \"--agent-name\", \"test-agent\"\n    ])\n    assert result.exit_code == 0\n    assert \"Successfully packaged agent\" in result.stdout\n\ndef test_pack_command_invalid_workspace():\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\n        \"pack\",\n        \"--workspace\", \"/nonexistent/path\"\n    ])\n    assert result.exit_code == 1\n    assert \"Error\" in result.stdout\n```\n\n### Integration Testing\n\n**Test Structure**:\n```\nmanifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/\n├── test_token_automount.sh\n├── test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh\n├── test_least_privilege.sh\n├── test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\n├── test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n├── test_router_permissions.sh\n├── test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n├── controller-manager_test.yaml\n├── router_test.yaml\n├── workload-manager_test.yaml\n└── rbac_test.yaml\n```\n\n**Test Framework**: Bash scripts + Kubernetes client\n\n**Key Test Areas**:\n1. RBAC permissions verification\n2. Service account token mounting\n3. Custom resource creation and reconciliation\n4. Pod lifecycle management\n5. Network policies\n6. Resource quotas\n\n**Example Test**:\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\necho \"Testing RBAC permissions for Controller Manager...\"\n\n# Create test namespace\nkubectl create namespace test-rbac-$(date +%s) || true\n\n# Deploy controller-manager with limited permissions\nhelm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n  --namespace test-rbac \\\n  --set controllerManager.enabled=true \\\n  --set controllerManager.serviceAccount.create=true\n\n# Verify permissions\nkubectl auth can-i get agentruntimes --namespace test-rbac\nkubectl auth can-i update codeinterpreters --namespace test-rbac\n\n# Clean up\nhelm uninstall agentcube --namespace test-rbac\nkubectl delete namespace test-rbac\n\necho \"RBAC test passed!\"\n```\n\n### End-to-End Testing\n\n**Test Scenarios**:\n\n1. **Complete Agent Lifecycle**:\n   - Create agent workspace\n   - Pack workspace\n   - Build image\n   - Publish to Kubernetes\n   - Invoke agent\n   - Query status\n   - Delete agent\n\n2. **Code Interpreter Session**:\n   - Create interpreter session\n   - Execute commands\n   - Write/read files\n   - Upload/download files\n   - Delete session\n\n3. **Agent Runtime Invocation**:\n   - Bootstrap session\n   - Send multiple requests\n   - Handle errors\n   - Session expiration\n\n**Test Framework**: Python with `pytest` + `kind` (Kubernetes in Docker)\n\n**Example Test**:\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.cli.main import app\nfrom typer.testing import CliRunner\n\n@pytest.mark.e2e\ndef test_complete_agent_lifecycle():\n    runner = CliRunner()\n    \n    # 1. Create workspace\n    workspace = Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\")\n    workspace.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n    (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text('print(\"Hello, World!\")')\n    \n    # 2. Pack\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"pack\", \"--workspace\", str(workspace)])\n    assert result.exit_code == 0\n    \n    # 3. Build\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\"build\", \"--workspace\", str(workspace)])\n    assert result.exit_code == 0\n    \n    # 4. Publish\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\n        \"publish\",\n        \"--workspace\", str(workspace),\n        \"--provider\", \"k8s\",\n        \"--namespace\", \"test-e2e\"\n    ])\n    assert result.exit_code == 0\n    \n    # 5. Invoke\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\n        \"invoke\",\n        \"--workspace\", str(workspace),\n        '--payload', '{\"message\": \"test\"}',\n        \"--provider\", \"k8s\"\n    ])\n    assert result.exit_code == 0\n    \n    # 6. Status\n    result = runner.invoke(app, [\n        \"status\",\n        \"--workspace\", str(workspace),\n        \"--provider\", \"k8s\"\n    ])\n    assert result.exit_code == 0\n    assert \"running\" in result.stdout.lower()\n    \n    # Clean up\n    import subprocess\n    subprocess.run([\"kubectl\", \"delete\", \"deployment\", \"test-agent\", \"-n\", \"test-e2e\"])\n```\n\n### Performance Testing\n\n**Metrics to Monitor**:\n1. API response times (p50, p95, p99)\n2. Session creation latency\n3. Command execution duration\n4. File upload/download throughput\n5. Memory usage\n6. CPU utilization\n7. Concurrent request handling\n\n**Tools**:\n- `locust` for load testing\n- `prometheus` + `grafana` for monitoring\n- `pprof` for profiling\n\n**Example Locust Test**:\n```python\nfrom locust import HttpUser, task, between\n\nclass AgentCubeUser(HttpUser):\n    wait_time = between(1, 3)\n    \n    def on_start(self):\n        self.session_id = self.create_session()\n    \n    @task\n    def execute_command(self):\n        self.client.post(\n            f\"/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/test/invocations/api/execute\",\n            json={\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"},\n            headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": self.session_id}\n        )\n    \n    def create_session(self):\n        response = self.client.post(\n            \"/v1/code-interpreter\",\n            json={\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"default\", \"ttl\": 3600}\n        )\n        return response.json()[\"sessionId\"]\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Unit Tests | Integration Tests | E2E Tests |\n|-----------|------------|-------------------|-----------|\n| Python SDK | 80%+ | N/A | N/A |\n| CLI | 70%+ | N/A | N/A |\n| Providers | 75%+ | 50%+ | N/A |\n| Services | 80%+ | N/A | N/A |\n| Controllers | 60%+ | 70%+ | 40%+ |\n| Router | 70%+ | 60%+ | 40%+ |\n| Store | 80%+ | 60%+ | 40%+ |\n| Picod | 75%+ | 60%+ | 40%+ |\n\n### Continuous Integration\n\n**CI Pipeline**:\n1. **Linting**: `flake8`, `black`, `isort`, `golint`, `gofmt`\n2. **Static Analysis**: `mypy`, `pylint`, `go vet`\n3. **Unit Tests**: Run with coverage reporting\n4. **Integration Tests**: Run against `kind` cluster\n5. **E2E Tests**: Run on test environment\n6. **Security Scans**: `trivy`, `gosec`, `bandit`\n7. **Build**: Docker images, CLI binaries\n8. **Publish**: Push to registry, GitHub releases\n\n**Pre-commit Hooks**:\n```yaml\nrepos:\n  - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks\n    hooks:\n      - id: trailing-whitespace\n      - id: end-of-file-fixer\n      - id: check-yaml\n      - id: check-added-large-files\n  - repo: https://github.com/psf/black\n    hooks:\n      - id: black\n  - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/isort\n    hooks:\n      - id: isort\n  - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/flake8\n    hooks:\n      - id: flake8\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication & Authorization\n\n1. **Kubernetes Service Accounts**: Use RBAC for API authentication\n2. **JWT Tokens**: Session-based authentication with time-limited tokens\n3. **Network Policies**: Restrict pod-to-pod communication\n4. **Secrets Management**: Use Kubernetes Secrets or external secret stores\n\n### Input Validation\n\n1. **Session ID Validation**: UUID format checking\n2. **Command Validation**: Whitelist allowed commands\n3. **File Path Validation**: Prevent directory traversal\n4. **Payload Size Limits**: Maximum request body size\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\n1. **Request Throttling**: Per-session and per-user limits\n2. **Resource Quotas**: CPU, memory, and storage limits\n3. **Concurrency Limits**: Maximum concurrent sessions per user\n\n### Audit Logging\n\n1. **API Access Logs**: All API calls with timestamps\n2. **Session Lifecycle Logs**: Creation, updates, deletion\n3. **Command Execution Logs**: All commands executed in sessions\n4. **Error Logs**: All errors with stack traces\n\n## Deployment Strategy\n\n### Helm Chart\n\nThe platform is deployed using Helm charts with configurable values:\n\n```yaml\n# values.yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  image:\n    repository: agentcube/controller-manager\n    tag: v1.0.0\n\nrouter:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 3\n  image:\n    repository: agentcube/router\n    tag: v1.0.0\n\nworkloadManager:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  image:\n    repository: agentcube/workload-manager\n    tag: v1.0.0\n\nstorage:\n  type: redis\n  redis:\n    host: redis.default.svc.cluster.local\n    port: 6379\n    password: \"\"\n```\n\n### Upgrade Strategy\n\n1. **Rolling Updates**: Zero-downtime deployments\n2. **Database Migrations**: Versioned schema changes\n3. **Backward Compatibility**: Support old API versions\n4. **Blue-Green Deployments**: Gradual traffic shifting\n\n### Monitoring & Observability\n\n1. **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics for all components\n2. **Logging**: Structured logs with correlation IDs\n3. **Tracing**: Distributed tracing with OpenTelemetry\n4. **Health Checks**: readiness and liveness probes\n5. **Alerting**: PagerDuty/Slack integration for critical failures\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Multi-Cluster Support**: Deploy agents across multiple clusters\n2. **GPU Support**: GPU-accelerated code execution\n3. **Custom Runtime Support**: Support additional language runtimes\n4. **Session Persistence**: Long-running session state management\n5. **Collaboration Features**: Multi-user session sharing\n6. **Cost Optimization**: Resource usage optimization and billing\n7. **Advanced Security**: Fine-grained access control and audit trails","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/providers/k8s_provider.py\">\nERROR [52:32] \"CoreV1Api\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [53:32] \"AppsV1Api\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [296:10] Variable not allowed in type expression\nERROR [149:37] Cannot access attribute \"spec\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"spec\" is unknown\nERROR [149:37] \"spec\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [149:37] Cannot access attribute \"spec\" for class \"list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unkn